OL,3,CInflation eases and hopes rise - can
OL,4,Cthe economy turn a corner in 2026?
OL,6,FPrices for food and drink, clothing,
OL,7,Frestaurants and hotels looked slightly
OL,8,Fmore stable, as ITV News Business and
OL,9,FEconomics Editor Joel Hills reports
OL,11,FInflation is fading faster than
OL,12,Fexpected.
OL,14,FPrices did rise in November, but by
OL,15,Ffar less than forecasters had
OL,16,Fpencilled in. The headline annual rate
OL,17,Fof inflation fell sharply to 3.2%,
OL,18,Fdriven in large part by what appears
OL,19,Fto have been extensive Black Friday
OL,20,Fdiscounting.
